asar por alto QTc\\Nen pacientes con\\Nfármacos QT-prolongadores","guid":"AFsVItu0SrKGJvds0S9-Mw","children":[]},{"id":"280","parent":"270","text":"Subestimar ECG normal\\Nen contexto de DT","guid":"gEZ7_WjQSniY7Z8DjEEqTg","children":[]}]},{"id":"281","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"VYl-aMeWSzGL4cDLs9CbGQ","children":[{"id":"282","parent":"281","text":"ECG es CONFIRMATORIO\\N(alta Sp, baja Sn)\\N→ NUNCA descarta SCA\\Npor sí solo","guid":"eOwaFKpeQiqi-n6O4jGUxg","children":[]},{"id":"283","parent":"281","text":"Pattern recognition es\\Núltil pero peligroso\\Nsin lectura sistemática","guid":"UqPt62SrQeOdrQGAWBccYw","children":[]},{"id":"284","parent":"281","text":"ECG seriados (cada 15-30 min)\\N→ duplican rendimiento\\Nen DT no traumático","guid":"DjWZVcfPSI6_aMcOZFQDfA","children":[]},{"id":"285","parent":"281","text":"BCRI NUEVO + clínica\\N= STEMI hasta demostrar\\Nlo contrario","guid":"4Id7RoZrQrGsrvoFrMtRwQ","children":[]},{"id":"286","parent":"281","text":"Sgarbossa ≥3 puntos\\N→ IAM en BCRI","guid":"yI7XX6EcS3aQcaa0efNPqQ","children":[]},{"id":"287","parent":"281","text":"ST↑ aVR + ST↓ difuso\\N→ tronco / 3 vasos\\N→ revascularización urgente","guid":"zQs72zhkRPei3dfZvmmcMg","children":[]},{"id":"288","parent":"281","text":"Wellens = DA proximal\\Ncrítica → NO esfuerzo\\N→ coronariografía","guid":"f1e2FFDaTl64l8B4b1K9fg","children":[]},{"id":"289","parent":"281","text":"De Winter = equivalente\\NSTEMI → reperfusión","guid":"63YzGG6qTk63vdTYNW5-Jw","children":[]},{"id":"290","parent":"281","text":"Sgarbossa modificado\\N(Smith) supera al original","guid":"uL5-vHdfTC-dvWPZwkSbmA","children":[]},{"id":"291","parent":"281","text":"Onda Osborn → hipotermia\\Nuntil proven otherwise","guid":"JWrDepiQR0uEbgdv8-4hpw","children":[]},{"id":"292","parent":"281","text":"Onda epsilon → ARVD","guid":"LNhnpiKVSWmzYJKyfx2xuQ","children":[]},{"id":"293","parent":"281","text":"QTc >500 ms = riesgo\\NTdP → revisar fármacos\\Ny electrolitos","guid":"WFDKwoyVQs-o1KBi5PIdwA","children":[]},{"id":"294","parent":"281","text":"HiperK con T picuda\\Nes solo el comienzo\\N→ tratar ANTES de\\NQRS ancho","guid":"guXv-JsGQzSXPUYxQ5o9rw","children":[]},{"id":"295","parent":"281","text":"Brugada algoritmo WCT\\N→ Sn 0.987 / Sp 0.965\\N→ herramienta más útil\\Nen TV vs aberrancia","guid":"XwdKmX3lQkSaoOPipemKMQ","children":[]},{"id":"296","parent":"281","text":"LR del ECG depende del\\Nhallazgo, no del trazado\\Nentero → razonar por\\Npatrones individuales","guid":"okJWvphSSGOMTIEEwsZu4w","children":[]},{"id":"297","parent":"281","text":"Imágenes de patrones\\Nclave (STEMI, Wellens,\\NDe Winter, Sgarbossa,\\NBrugada, Osborn, epsilon,\\NhiperK, S1Q3T3) → revisar\\NLITFL, ECG Wave-Maven\\Ny atlas Goldberger","guid":"I62dyzqWRE2cUCWnuONnRA","children":[]},{"id":"298","parent":"281","text":"Referencias","guid":"_V9vTMa7QOajq_Wk-FMpSQ","children":[{"id":"299","parent":"298","text":"1. Surawicz B, Childers R, Deal BJ, et al. AHA/ACCF/HRS recommendations for the standardization and interpretation of the electrocardiogram: part III: intraventricular conduction disturbances. J Am Coll Cardiol. 2009;53(11):976-81.","guid":"k-aAJ3pHReKvMuuQ-tLL0g","children":[]},{"id":"300","parent":"298","text":"2. Brugada P, Brugada J, Mont L, et al. A new approach to the differential diagnosis of a regular tachycardia with a wide QRS complex. Circulation. 1991;83(5):1649-59.","guid":"pK6loUnWS3CSROdWQ5uiTA","children":[]},{"id":"301","parent":"298","text":"3. Roffi M, Patrono C, Collet JP, et al. 2015 ESC Guidelines for the management of acute coronary syndromes in patients presenting without persistent ST-segment elevation. Eur Heart J. 2016;37(3):267-315.","guid":"asKgY0aIQR6iki48qi8YFA","children":[]},{"id":"302","parent":"298","text":"4. Ibanez B, James S, Agewall S, et al. 2017 ESC Guidelines for the management of acute myocardial infarction in patients presenting with ST-segment elevation. Eur Heart J. 2018;39(2):119-177.","guid":"X9mM7Cp6Q52vwBYlsvyZbw","children":[]},{"id":"303","parent":"298","text":"5. Thygesen K, Alpert JS, Jaffe AS, et al. Fourth Universal Definition of Myocardial Infarction (2018). Circulation. 2018;138(20):e618-e651.","guid":"oJxtpXrbRyyI1leSDq5dZQ","children":[]},{"id":"304","parent":"298","text":"6. Smith SW, Dodd KW, Henry TD, et al. Diagnosis of ST-elevation myocardial infarction in the presence of left bundle branch block with the ST-elevation to S-wave ratio in a modified Sgarbossa rule. Ann Emerg Med. 2012;60(6):766-76.","guid":"d20hw_IaTUmbiv4v_sg5iQ","children":[]},{"id":"305","parent":"298","text":"7. de Winter RJ, Verouden NJ, Wellens HJ, Wilde AA. A new ECG sign of proximal LAD occlusion. N Engl J Med. 2008;359(19):2071-3.","guid":"8isWbkdlR7GxUPCoCZPLfA","children":[]},{"id":"306","parent":"298","text":"8. Surawicz B, Knilans T. Chou's Electrocardiography in Clinical Practice. 6th ed. Philadelphia: Saunders; 2008.","guid":"iG7YBy3VTWqS7-fDpocPzA","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":306,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"MUE - Medicina de Urgencia","filename":"MUE_ECG","id":"map_2502","resolved_references":[]}